cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.NI, cs.OS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about scheduling jobs in a cluster.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a new scheduler that dynamically resizes the cluster to handle bursty workloads.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed scheduler in terms of job performance and resource cost.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) may be relevant as the paper deals with managing resources in a datacenter.
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) may also be relevant as the paper proposes a new scheduler for managing resources in a cluster.
